This paper is about learning phrase representations for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of gated recurrent units (GRUs) suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which is also reflected in the likely sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions phrase similarity tasks, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of large-scale paraphrase databases suggests a potential focus on neural embeddings, which could also fall under neural networks (cs.NE).
